      "id": "PopularPost91156",
      "post_content": "The oracle text usually follows the intentions of the last card printing. (They have noted that fifth edition printings sometimes have exceptions.) In Sixth edition, all sort of changes were made, to the game -- first edition to use a stack mechanic -- and existing cards. For example, before Sixth Edition your [Flying Carpet](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flying Carpet) would go down in flames with the creature using it, like most proto-equipment did. It's the only edition I know of where someone looked at existing cards, said \"that's not nearly good enough,\" and rewrote them rather than print an updated version with a different name and text.",
      "posted_by": "longwinded",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost91156\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">The oracle text usually follows the intentions of the last card printing. (They have noted that fifth edition printings sometimes have exceptions.) In Sixth edition, all sort of changes were made, to the game -- first edition to use a stack mechanic -- and existing cards. For example, before Sixth Edition your <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Flying Carpet\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flying Carpet\">Flying Carpet</a> would go down in flames with the creature using it, like most proto-equipment did. It's the only edition I know of where someone looked at existing cards, said \"that's not nearly good enough,\" and rewrote them rather than print an updated version with a different name and text.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '91156'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy40319\">longwinded</span>\r\n                                (7/26/2010 3:45:46 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"c